lines.text: Cookies and cream, Big Dog?
This isn't an intensive care and your feet aren't plastered to cement. Come on back here and help yourself. I'm busy!
[Trivette walks behind counter]
I'd like some coffee!
Sure, customer! Coming right up!
[Alex walks in]
Hey guys!
Would you like some coffee?
How about a cruise for our honeymoon?
We've already done that.
That was a river raft!
Close enough.
I'd like a soda, C.D...
Is your foot in a bear trap? You've been comin' here long enough. Get your own soda.

[calming down the rowdy patrons of a bar]
Careful boys. Little girl with a gun.

[undercover]
I got another gun you can play with.
Sorry, but I prefer something in a bigger caliber.

[Alex is pregnant]
Hey, Honey, how are you feeling?
[Alex covers her mouth with her hand and runs to the bathroom]
Sydney, how long is this morning sickness suppose to last?
How should I know?
All I know is, I'm glad women have to go through this and not men!
Men are such wimps!
[walks off to go find Alex]

[agreeing]
Well... Yep. Yeah. Sure.
[after being beaten up by Walker]
I'm glad he's in a happy mood.
[Sydney and Gage prepare to make dinner]
So who's cooking and who's cleaning?
Can you cook?
Are you kidding? I'm a bachelor. Of course I can cook!
Okay, so what can you cook?
French toast.
French toast? Is that all?
Cinnamon toast.
Cinnamon toast.
Raisin toast. (pause) Rye toast.
(stares blankly)
You cook. I'll clean.

[Sydney is chasing gangsters. They try to jump a fence to get away from her]
Don't MAKE me climb that fence!

[pacing in front of three bank robbers who are sitting on the curb, hands cuffed behind thier backs]
You are under arrest for robbery, assault on a peace officer and for making me miss the rodeo!

[Walker and Alex are choosing silverware and china]
Do you see anything that jumps out at you? Is anything speaking to you?
Yeah, they're speaking to me. But they're speaking in French, so I can't understand what they're saying.
Very funny.
You can't leave, we're at Defcon One.
You guys really talk like that?
[Sydney and Jimmy come out of a piercing parlor after interviewing someone; she hints he should pierce something]
Yeah, right. If I'd get an ear pierced, Walker'd make me ride in the back of his truck.
[Walker carries bad guys to jail by placing them in the back of his truck]
Sydney, Gage, you're going undercover at the bar. Gage, you're going to be a bartender. Sydney...
I know, I know. Cocktail waitress.

[Walker has just saved Alex after the river rafting trip]
Next time, we go to Disneyland.
No way!... I'm afraid of the rides!

[to Alex after she tastes his chili, and says it not hot]
Were you born on the sun, honey?

[Jimmy is trying to bring C.D. into the information age]
I don't need the internet. When I was a kid, My mother only had a phone... She never took calls after 8 p.m.
Did it have a crank?
What did you just call me?
